<section class="section">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h1>About Observable Compute Foundation</h1>
    <p class="lead">Observable Compute Foundation is a South Dakota 501(c)(3) nonprofit dedicated to independent AI research, expanding technology access in rural and underserved communities, and developing free educational resources for workers affected by AI-driven displacement.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>We study what AI systems actually do — measurable behavior, documented function, no hype. Our research focuses on the communities most affected by AI-driven workforce displacement: rural towns, tribal nations, and economically vulnerable populations that receive limited attention from larger institutions.</p>

    <p>Everything we publish is free and open access. We believe the communities most impacted by AI deserve the best information about it.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h2>What We Do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Conduct original AI research</strong> on observable function, workforce displacement, and rural economic impact — all published freely through SSRN and our website</li>
      <li><strong>Provide free AI literacy resources</strong> including practical guides, tool directories, and educational primers</li>
      <li><strong>Deliver community technology education</strong> through in-person workshops at public libraries, tribal colleges, and community centers across western South Dakota</li>
      <li><strong>Track terminology evolution</strong> across research, legal, industry, and public domains through our Living Lexicon</li>
      <li><strong>Publish quarterly reports</strong> with transparent methodology and open data</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

